$ SQL Server - T-SQL / statements

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/alter/database[`alter database …`]

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/bulk-insert[`bulk insert`] to insert → development/Data/exchange/formats/CSV[CSV] data into a table.

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables/declare[`declare`] is needed to declare → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables[variables] or
→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/cursors[cursors].

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/execute[`execute`]

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/if[`if`] to conditionally execute statements depending on a boolean expression.

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/kill[`kill`] terminates processes.

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/reconfigure[`reconfigure`], apparently needed sometimes after executing → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/stored-procedures/sp_configure[`sp_configure`].

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/set[`set`] to assign values to → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/variables[variables] or to set boolean-like session options.

Wait (sleep) for a given amount of time with → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/waitfor/delay[waitfor delay].

Report exceptions with the → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/throw[`throw`] statement.

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/while[`while`] to iterate over a block of statements until a certain condition becomse false.
 
